\f1\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 \ulnone Name: 2dSearch\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: 2dSearch offers a new approach to search strategy development in which concepts are expressed as objects on a two-dimensional canvas and relationships are expressed using direct manipulation. Interactive query suggestions are provided using machine learning techniques combined with ontology lookup. This approach eliminates many sources of syntactic error, makes the query semantics more transparent, and offers new ways to validate, debug and share search strategies and best practices.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.2dsearch.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Abstrackr\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: An online tool for the task of citation screening for systematic reviews.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://abstrackr.cebm.brown.edu/account/login"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Screen\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Amamida R Package\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Amanida R package is a meta-analysis approach using only the most reported statistical parameters in the field of metabolomics: p-value and fold-change. The p-values are combined via Fisher\'92s method and fold-changes are combined by averaging, both weighted by the study size (n). The amanida package includes several visualization options: a volcano plot for quantitative results, a vote plot for total regulation behaviors (up/down regulations) for each compound, and an explore plot of the vote-counting results with the number of times a compound is found upregulated or downregulated.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/amanida/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Synthesis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: AND - Author Name Disambiguation\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Author-centric analyses of fast-growing biomedical reference databases are challenging due to author ambiguity. This problem has been mainly addressed through author disambiguation using supervised machine-learning algorithms. Such algorithms, however, require adequately designed gold standards that reflect the reference database properly. The developers of AND used MEDLINE to build the first unbiased gold standard in a reference database and improve over the existing state of the art in author disambiguation. May be useful for supplementary search methods such as key author searching, particularly where authors have relatively common names. The principles and methods can be applied to other reference databases beyond MEDLINE. The gold standard and code used for this study are available via the GitHub repository.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/amorgani/AND/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: AntConc\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: A freeware corpus analysis toolkit for concordancing and text analysis.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.laurenceanthony.net/software/antconc/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Screen\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: BeCAS\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: BeCAS, the Biomedical Concept Annotation System, is a web application, application programming interface (API) and widget for biomedical concept identification. BeCAS aims to help researchers, healthcare professionals and developers in the identification of over 1,200,000 biomedical concepts in text and PubMed abstracts using text-mining capabilities. Details of how to use the web app are available in the help section of the tool. If you want to integrate BeCAS annotation services in your own text-processing pipeline, this can be done via the API. Web developers can augment websites with text annotation and highlighting capabilities using the BeCAS widget. BeCAS is freely available for non-commercial use.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://bioinformatics.ua.pt/becas/#!/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search, Screen, Data Extract\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: BERT\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) is a tool developed by researchers at Google AI Language. BERT is a machine learning tool that can be used in a wide variety of NLP tasks, including Question Answering, Natural Language Inference, and others.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/google-research/bert"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Screen, Data Extract\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Citavi\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: A commercial reference management tool with knowledge management facilities.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.citavi.com/en/features.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Reference Management\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Colandr\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Colandr is an open access, machine-learning assisted tool for conducting evidence synthesis. This tool uses machine learning, natural language processing, and text-mining functions to partially automate finding relevant citations and extract desired data from PDF articles.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.colandrapp.com/signin"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search, Screen, Data Extract\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Comprehensive Meta-Analysis (CMA)\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Software package for meta-analysis.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.meta-analysis.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Synthesis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Cytoscape\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Cytoscape is an open source software platform for complex network analysis and visualization. Originally designed for biological research, it is now a general platform for data integration, analysis, and visualization. There is a manual, tutorials and demos available on the Cytoscape website. Additional features are available as Apps, such as network and molecular profiling analyses, new layouts, additional file format support, scripting, and connection with databases. Most of the Apps are freely available from Cytoscape App Store. Apps may be developed by anyone using the Cytoscape open API based on Java\'99 technology and App community development is encouraged.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cytoscape.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Synthesis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: AlvisIR Food semantic search engine\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: The AlvisIR Food semantic search engine presents and indexes the results of a text mining process using the Alvis text mining platform to automatically and efficiently find relevant information in the food microbiology domain. The search engine is publicly available via a web browser and can be used to search for information about microorganism phenotypes and habitats. AlvisIR interprets user query terms as taxonomy or ontology concepts, and expands each term with synonyms and more specific concepts in their respective hierarchies. The search results contain all documents (all PubMed abstracts indexed by MeSH terms related to microorganisms or food) that have been annotated through the text mining process.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bibliome.jouy.inra.fr/demo/food/alvisir/webapi/search"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: ASReview\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: ASReview LAB is free and open source machine learning software, dedicated to accelerate the screening of textual data. The software comes with a modern user-friendly interface for screening texts, as well as an extensive simulation toolkit. Use simulations to explore how much work you can save by using ASReview LAB over manual screening. The software is installed locally, making sure that your data stays your own.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://asreview.nl/#!/up"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Screen\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: BibDesk\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: An open source reference management software package for Mac OS X with, primarily, a BibTeX front-end for use with LaTeX.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://bibdesk.sourceforge.io/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Reference Management\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Carrot2\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Carrot2 is an Open Source Search Results Clustering Engine. It can automatically organise relatively small collections of documents (search results) into thematic categories. Carrot2 algorithms perform in-memory clustering and should successfully deal with up to a thousand of documents, of a few paragraphs each.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/carrot2/carrot2"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Cientopolis Scolr\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Cientopolis Scolr supports collaboration in the process of conducting open, literature reviews.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://scolr.cientopolis.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Protocol, Search, Screen, Data Extract, Quality Assess, Synthesis, Report, Reference Management, Stakeholder Engagement\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: CINeMA\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: CINeMA (Confidence in Network Meta-Analysis) is a web application that applies the Salanti approach to adapting the GRADE framework for network meta-analysis. Outputs a downloadable report with a summary of the evaluations.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cinema.ispm.unibe.ch/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Synthesis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: CitNetExplorer\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Tool for analyzing and visualizing citation networks.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.citnetexplorer.nl/features"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: CrowdCARE\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: CrowdCARE is a free, online tool developed by the University of Melbourne, to crowdsource critical appraisal of research. The developers have tested the validity of this approach to assess the methodological quality of systematic reviews.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://crowdcare.unimelb.edu.au/index.html?g=true&ts=1646416266186&page="}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Quality Assess\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: A2A (Apples to Apples)\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: A2A is a search and benchmarking tool which is publicly available for the researchers who want to explore different search strategies to retrieve published biomedical literature. It provides a web-based Graphical User Interface (GUI), allowing users to define and execute biomedical information retrieval (IR) experiments and explore their evaluation results. A2A enables the evaluation of query formulation techniques within a predefined, yet parameterisable, framework. A2A\'92s GUI provides access to an extensible Python-based pipeline system which instantiates and evaluates IR systems with pre-indexed TREC collections, including a snapshot of PubMed articles. This means users can establish baselines and evaluate query expansion strategies. In order to use A2A, users will need to register for an online account on the system.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://a2a.csiro.au/benchmarking/about"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Automatic VAriant evidence DAtabase (AVADA)\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Automatic VAriant evidence DAtabase (AVADA) is a machine learning tool that uses natural language processing to automatically identify pathogenic genetic variant evidence in full-text primary literature about monogenic disease and convert it to genomic coordinates. AVADA aims to advance automated retrieval of pathogenic monogenic variant evidence from full-text literature. The authors state it is "far from perfect" but that it is much faster than PubMed/Google Scholar search. Careful curation of AVADA-retrieved evidence can aid both database curation and ultimately patient diagnosis.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bejerano.stanford.edu/AVADA/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: BADERI\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: BADERI is an internet-based platform to coordinate handsearching activities to identify controlled clinical trials for their potential inclusion in systematic reviews. Access is free, but a login and password must be requested.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.baderi.com/login.php"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: BEST (Biomedical Entity Search Tool)\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: BEST is a next-generation biomedical entity search tool for knowledge discovery in PubMed. BEST utilizes text-mining approaches to extract biomedical entities from PubMed abstracts. Using a novel indexing and scoring scheme, BEST indexes 10 different types of biomedical entities (e.g., genes, diseases, drugs, targets, transcription factors, miRNAs, and mutations) from the entire PubMed corpus. BEST processes users\'92 free text queries and returns up-to-date results in real time. Results are displayed by relevance and categorised by entity, meaning results can be navigated, allowing for quick scoping of the literature and the potential to prioritise results for screening.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/dmis-lab/bio-entity-extractor"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Bibus\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Bibliographic and reference management software.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bibus-biblio.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Main_Page"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Reference Management\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: BioReader (Biomedical Research Article Distiller)\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: BioReader is a tool that enables users to perform classification of scientific literature by text mining-based classification of article abstracts. The tool is trained by uploading article corpora for two training categories - e.g. one positive and one negative for content of interest - as well as one corpus of abstracts to be classified and/or a search string to query PubMed for articles. The corpora are submitted as lists of PubMed IDs and the abstracts are automatically downloaded from PubMed, preprocessed, and the unclassified corpus is classified using the best performing classification algorithm out of ten implemented algorithms. BioReader is freely available as a web service.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://services.healthtech.dtu.dk/service.php?BioReader-1.2"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Screen\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Citation and Text-Based Framework for Retrieving Publications for Literature Reviews\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: A citation- and text-based framework to conduct literature review searches, which is in its first implementation. The proposed framework retrieves papers from a set of seed articles through citation relationships, then ?lters the papers using citation and text-based methods. Further testing of the performance and utility of the framework is warranted, but preliminary results suggest that a hybrid citation- and text-based approach can be a useful strategy in supporting literature reviews.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/janinaj/lit-review-search"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: colwiz\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Reference management software incorporating collaboration, networking and productivity features.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.wizdom.ai/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Reference Management\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Comparative Toxigenomics Database (CTD)\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: CTD is a publicly available database that aims to advance understanding about how environmental exposures affect human health. It provides manually curated information about chemical\'96gene/protein interactions, chemical\'96disease and gene\'96disease relationships. These data are integrated with functional and pathway data to aid in development of hypotheses about the mechanisms underlying environmentally influenced diseases. Direct links to the relevant literature are included via DOIs and PubMed IDs. CTD may be a useful resource for systematic reviews relating to environmental exposures and the effect on general health or specific outcomes.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://ctdbase.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Protocol, Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Concept Encoder\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Concept Encoder is a neural network\'96based artificial intelligence engine that analyses text by converting sentences into vectors. extract and learn each vector component as a feature value, identify similar vectors as indicators of the similarity of sentence content, and perform a rapid search for similar sentences. As such, it can be used to reduce the screening workload in systematic reviews. Note that the research study was performed in systematic reviews for clinical guidelines and the authors state that further investigation is needed to assess the effectiveness for meta-analyses of epidemiological studies.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.fronteo.com/en/products/conceptencoder/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Screen\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Confidence Interval Calculator\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: An Excel spreadsheet that can be used to calculate confidence intervals for a mean, the difference between two means, a proportion or odds, comparisons of two proportions (the absolute risk reduction, number needed to treat, relative risk, relative risk reduction and odds ratio), sensitivity, specificity and two-level likelihood ratios.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://pedro.org.au/english/resources/confidence-interval-calculator/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Mixed Method\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Synthesis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Coremine Medical\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Coremine presents search results as a graphic network that describes relationships discovered through text-mining. Relationship networks provide an overview of a topic by clustering important terms. The network is also a navigational tool that can help searchers explore concepts related to their search term (the graphic is hyperlinked to source information). The text records indexed are those comprising the MEDLINE database (i.e. titles and abstracts contained in PubMed).\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://coremine.com/medical/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Qualitative, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf4 \cb5 Name: Covidence\cf6 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: A web-based software platform that streamlines the production of systematic reviews, including Cochrane Reviews. Citation screening, Full text review, Risk of Bias assessment, Extraction of study characteristics and other study data, Export of data into RevMan. Nonprofit organization, open source software\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.covidence.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
