\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: CLAMP is a comprehensive clinical Natural Language Processing (NLP) software that enables recognition and automatic encoding of clinical information in narrative patient reports. It can also be used to mine full text journal articles and abstracts, for example from PubMed. CLAMP provides NLP components, but also a user-friendly graphic user interface that can help users quickly build customized NLP pipelines for their individual applications. CLAMP is publicly available for research use. CLAMP is a comprehensive clinical Natural Language Processing (NLP) software that enables recognition and automatic encoding of clinical information in narrative patient reports. It can also be used to mine full text journal articles and abstracts, for example from PubMed. CLAMP provides NLP components, but also a user-friendly graphic user interface that can help users quickly build customized NLP pipelines for their individual applications. CLAMP is publicly available for research use.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://clamp.uth.edu/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Qualitative, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Data Extract, Synthesis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

