\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \cb5 Summary: Proteomics and genomics discovery experiments generate increasingly large result tables, necessitating more researcher time to convert the biological data into new knowledge. Literature review is an important step in this process. To streamline and formalise this process of literature retrieval and analysis of discovery based \'91omics data and as a decision-facilitating support tool for follow-up experiments, OmixLitMiner has been created, a package written in the computational language R. The tool automates the retrieval of literature from PubMed based on UniProt protein identifiers, gene names and their synonyms, combined with user defined contextual keyword search (i.e., gene ontology based). The search strategy is programmed to allow either focused or broader literature retrieval and the outputs are assigned to three categories describing how well characterized a regulated gene or protein is. The category helps to meet a decision, regarding which gene/protein follow-up experiments may be performed for gaining new knowledge and to exclude following already known biomarkers.\cb1 \
\cb5 URL: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/Sydney-Informatics-Hub/OmixLitMiner"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 Link}}\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Families: Systematic, Rapid, Scoping, Mapping, Mixed Method, Review Of Reviews, Other\cb1 \
\cb5 Review Stages: Search\cb1 \
